container
------------
1. A container is a running instance of an image 
2. An application running in a container can only modify the container layers
3. content stored in this container layers it is lost when container is no longer running 

To create a container with random name 
	
	$ docker container create my-image

To create a container with custome name
	
	$ docker container create --name my-container my-image

Note: shortcut for ($ docker container create) is ($ docker create)
	
To rename docker container 
	
	$ docker container rename my-old-container my-new-container

To list container 
	
	$ docker container ls

To list all contaiers 
	
	$ docker container ls --list  